        <h4>Ordinal Challenge</h4>
          <p>This Ruby program will convert a plain number to the ordinal number. So for example, if the user
          enters 2, it will display 2nd, if the user enters 3, it will display 3rd, etc </p>

        <pre><code class="language-ruby coding-example">
puts &quot;Enter a number:&quot;
number = gets.chomp
val = number.to_i

ord =  val % 10 
ordsecond = val % 100

if number == &quot;11&quot; || number == &quot;12&quot;
|| number == &quot;13&quot;
puts &quot;That's the #{number}th item&quot;
elsif ord == 1 
puts &quot;That's the #{number}st item&quot;
elsif ord == 1 &amp;&amp; ordsecond == 1
puts &quot;That's the #{number}th item&quot;
elsif ord == 2 &amp;&amp; ordsecond != 1
puts &quot;That's the #{number}nd item&quot;
elsif ord == 3 
puts &quot;That's the #{number}rd item&quot;
else
puts &quot;That's the #{number}th item&quot;
end
      </code></pre>
