      <h4>Foobar</h4>
        <p>This Ruby program is an adaptation of a classic technical interview problem which displays
        sequences of the Foobar pattern.</p>
   
      <pre><code class="language-ruby coding-example">
puts &quot;How many items they want to see?&quot;
items = gets.chomp.to_i
numbers = (1..items)
numbers.each do |num|

if num % 3 == 0 &amp;&amp; num % 5 == 0
puts &quot;FooBar&quot;
elsif num % 3 == 0
puts &quot;Foo&quot;
elsif num % 5 == 0
puts &quot;Bar&quot;
else
puts num
end
end
      </code></pre>
